I would caution against using the FMS to find out the alliance color at boot up  to determine the alliance color as described in the sample code for PP for setupPathPlanner(). Specifically this code…

var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance(); return alliance.isPresent() ? alliance.get() == DriverStation.Alliance.Red : false;

We had two different tournaments where the robot was on the red side, and it ran the blue version. One of those matches I know there was some sort of issue with the FMS that delayed the start of the match. I checked with our other two alliance partners who are running PP as well, and they did not have issues while we did. The difference is that they don’t rely on the FMS to tell them the alliance color to determine if the red or blue versions of the paths are loaded. We will be changing our code and no longer relying on the FMS at boot-time when calling setupPathPlanner().
